    slug: 'how-to-make-a-diy-photography-studio-track-lighting-suspension-system-using-strut',
    title: `How to Make a DIY Photography Studio Track-Lighting Suspension System Using Strut`,
    excerpt: `This post outlines how I built a moving-track overhead lighting grid for my photography studio.`,
    date: '2025-04-28',
    author: 'Andrew Petrov',
    category: 'DIY',
    image: 'https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5ade3b6aaa49a154ddb7e2bc/1bc491a8-8c48-4674-80c3-934107214ede/IMG_6636+copy-topaz-denoise.jpg',
    images: ["https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5ade3b6aaa49a154ddb7e2bc/1bc491a8-8c48-4674-80c3-934107214ede/IMG_6636+copy-topaz-denoise.jpg"],
    content: `<p>This post outlines how I built a moving-track overhead lighting grid for my photography studio.</p><p>This system lets you roll lights anywhere above a set forabout one-tenth the price of a comparable Manfrotto Sky Track—and the layout can grow indefinitely by adding more channel and trolleys.</p><p>This system is built completely from components available at any home center like Home Depot or Lowes, and from Amazon.</p><p>The main rails are attached directly to the ceiling joists using standard construction screws. They were painted black using standard Rustoleum spray paint.</p><p>Superstrut 10 ft half-slotted channel– primary rails, painted flat-black after installation#9 × 2 ½″ star-drive construction screws– mount channel directly to ceiling joistsLimit-stop wheels– keep moving rails from overrunning the track</p><li>Superstrut 10 ft half-slotted channel– primary rails, painted flat-black after installation</li><p>Superstrut 10 ft half-slotted channel– primary rails, painted flat-black after installation</p><li>#9 × 2 ½″ star-drive construction screws– mount channel directly to ceiling joists</li><p>#9 × 2 ½″ star-drive construction screws– mount channel directly to ceiling joists</p><li>Limit-stop wheels– keep moving rails from overrunning the track</li><p>Limit-stop wheels– keep moving rails from overrunning the track</p><h2>Moving rails</h2><p>Each moving rail is hung using a combination of trolley hangers and strut hangers, both of which are available on Amazon.</p><p>SKTREX strut hangers– bolt to fixed rails and hold the rolling rails4-wheel heavy-duty trolleys– let each secondary rail glide end-to-end</p><li>SKTREX strut hangers– bolt to fixed rails and hold the rolling rails</li><p>SKTREX strut hangers– bolt to fixed rails and hold the rolling rails</p><li>4-wheel heavy-duty trolleys– let each secondary rail glide end-to-end</li><p>4-wheel heavy-duty trolleys– let each secondary rail glide end-to-end</p><p>Boom arms are mounted to the 12-wheel trollies using 1/4-inch bolts and washers.</p><p>Hoist Trolley for PA200-1000Selens 22″ boom armSelens 39″ boom arm</p><li>Hoist Trolley for PA200-1000</li><p>Hoist Trolley for PA200-1000</p><li>Selens 22″ boom arm</li><p>Selens 22″ boom arm</p><li>Selens 39″ boom arm</li><p>Selens 39″ boom arm</p><h3>Light Fixtures</h3><p>Aputure Amaran 300c- Used as a key, primarily with shoot-through umbrellasAputure Amaran 150c- Used as a fill with aNeewer 28” softboxAputure Amaran 150c- Usex as a pair of kicker or background lightsAputure Amaran 60x- used for a hairlight with a 24 inch beauty dish</p><li>Aputure Amaran 300c- Used as a key, primarily with shoot-through umbrellas</li><p>Aputure Amaran 300c- Used as a key, primarily with shoot-through umbrellas</p><li>Aputure Amaran 150c- Used as a fill with aNeewer 28” softbox</li><p>Aputure Amaran 150c- Used as a fill with aNeewer 28” softbox</p><li>Aputure Amaran 150c- Usex as a pair of kicker or background lights</li><p>Aputure Amaran 150c- Usex as a pair of kicker or background lights</p><li>Aputure Amaran 60x- used for a hairlight with a 24 inch beauty dish</li><p>Aputure Amaran 60x- used for a hairlight with a 24 inch beauty dish</p><h3>Cable management</h3><p>Cables are managed using 2-wheel trollies and aluminum carabiners.</p><p>2-wheel trolley assemblies– ride the moving rails; each carries one boom arm3″ aluminum carabiners– clip to 2-wheel trolleys for clean cable support</p><li>2-wheel trolley assemblies– ride the moving rails; each carries one boom arm</li><p>2-wheel trolley assemblies– ride the moving rails; each carries one boom arm</p><li>3″ aluminum carabiners– clip to 2-wheel trolleys for clean cable support</li><p>3″ aluminum carabiners– clip to 2-wheel trolleys for clean cable support</p><h2>Assembly Outline</h2><p>Fasten fixed rails:drive star-head construction screws through the strut into ceiling joists; paint rails flat black.Add rolling hardware:bolt SKTREX hangers to the fixed rails and insert 4-wheel trolleys.Mount secondary rails:thread each hanging bracket into a trolley so the entire rail rolls across the room.Install stops:clamp limit-stop wheels to the parent track to define travel limits.Attach booms:secure each Selens boom to a 2-wheel trolley with a single ¼-20 bolt and lock-nut.Cable management:hook carabiners to the 2-wheel trolleys and run power cords through them.</p><li>Fasten fixed rails:drive star-head construction screws through the strut into ceiling joists; paint rails flat black.</li><p>Fasten fixed rails:drive star-head construction screws through the strut into ceiling joists; paint rails flat black.</p><li>Add rolling hardware:bolt SKTREX hangers to the fixed rails and insert 4-wheel trolleys.</li><p>Add rolling hardware:bolt SKTREX hangers to the fixed rails and insert 4-wheel trolleys.</p><li>Mount secondary rails:thread each hanging bracket into a trolley so the entire rail rolls across the room.</li><p>Mount secondary rails:thread each hanging bracket into a trolley so the entire rail rolls across the room.</p><li>Install stops:clamp limit-stop wheels to the parent track to define travel limits.</li><p>Install stops:clamp limit-stop wheels to the parent track to define travel limits.</p><li>Attach booms:secure each Selens boom to a 2-wheel trolley with a single ¼-20 bolt and lock-nut.</li><p>Attach booms:secure each Selens boom to a 2-wheel trolley with a single ¼-20 bolt and lock-nut.</p><li>Cable management:hook carabiners to the 2-wheel trolleys and run power cords through them.</li><p>Cable management:hook carabiners to the 2-wheel trolleys and run power cords through them.</p><p>Build time is about half a day with a drill and socket set; total cost lands well under 10 % of a commercial sky-track kit.</p><h2>Control & Power</h2><p>One wall switch:a single switched outlet powers the grid; flip it and every fixture comes online.Sidus Link app:intensity, CCT, hue, and effects for each Amaran head are adjusted wirelessly from a phone—no DMX runs, no physical dimmers.</p><li>One wall switch:a single switched outlet powers the grid; flip it and every fixture comes online.</li><p>One wall switch:a single switched outlet powers the grid; flip it and every fixture comes online.</p><li>Sidus Link app:intensity, CCT, hue, and effects for each Amaran head are adjusted wirelessly from a phone—no DMX runs, no physical dimmers.</li><p>Sidus Link app:intensity, CCT, hue, and effects for each Amaran head are adjusted wirelessly from a phone—no DMX runs, no physical dimmers.</p><h2>Infinite Expansion</h2><p>Need more reach or capacity? Add another length of strut, drop two more 4-wheel trolleys, and bolt it on. Extra 2-wheel trolleys create new light positions in seconds, and every component is standard Unistrut hardware—readily available and budget-friendly.</p><p>With basic hand tools and off-the-shelf parts, you get a silent, floor-free lighting system that slides wherever the shot demands—at a fraction of the cost of pre-built solutions and with unlimited room to grow.</p>`,
